# PHP Coding Standards & Learning Guidelines

## PHP Coding Standards:
- Follow PSR-12 coding standards
- Use 4-space indentation for PHP files
- Implement proper error handling with try-catch blocks
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Include proper docblocks for functions and classes
- Separate concerns and use proper file organization

## Security Considerations:
- Include proper security measures (input validation, XSS prevention)
- Never commit secrets, passwords, or sensitive data
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Implement proper input validation

## Learning and Development:
- Take notes on key concepts learned in each exercise
- Document any challenges faced and solutions found
- Keep track of useful kubectl commands and Docker tips
- Reference the course material and documentation
- Test thoroughly before considering an exercise complete

## Documentation Requirements:
- Document deployment steps and requirements
- Include example usage and configuration
- Explain the purpose of each exercise
- Document any special configuration or setup steps
- Include troubleshooting sections for common issues
